PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1773151902
OL,3,CWet start to year causes surge in
OL,4,Cdrivers hitting potholes hidden by
OL,5,Cpuddles
OL,7,FMr Williams described water as "the
OL,8,Fenemy of the roads" as it enters
OL,9,Fcracks and ` when the temperature
OL,10,Fdrops below 0C ` freezes and expands,
OL,11,Fcausing potholes.
OL,13,FHe continued: "Preventing water from
OL,14,Fsitting on our local roads is key to
OL,15,Ftheir long-term health, so it's vital
OL,16,Fmore work to improve drainage is
OL,17,Fcarried out.
OL,19,F"Without this, drivers will continue
OL,20,Fto have to fork out their hard-earned
OL,21,Fmoney on fixing their cars."
OL,26,@oD@`OUpD@SO]uD@OOU{D@AOU}D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
